{{Quote|Ah, but it was a sweet life, wasn't it, my friend? Low life expectancy, no bonuses, the contempt of our fellow citizens—you've got to admit, you miss it.|Swanny Mull, to Naatan tunnel-worker comrade Rorq|<ref name="Jedi Quest: The Shadow Trap">''[[Jedi Quest: The Shadow Trap]]''</ref>}}
'''Swanny Mull''' was a [[Mawan (species)|Mawan]] musician who founded the band [[Swanny and the Rooters]] shortly after the [[Battle of Naboo/Legends|Battle of Naboo]]. He frequently performed with his bandmates at [[Decca Besadii Diori|Decca]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt's]] headquarters.

In the years leading up to the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], Mull worked as a "water rat"—a wastewater systems programmer for the city of [[Naatan]] on his homeworld, [[Mawan/Legends|Mawan]].

In [[25 BBY/Legends|25 BBY]], Swanny and his tunnel-worker friend [[Rorq]] helped [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] to infiltrate Decca's stronghold; in return, the two [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] performed as part of his band at one of Decca's celebratory "revels," traditionally held after any defeat against Striker. Swanny was nearly killed, however, when a group of [[Granta Omega|Striker's]] men attacked Decca's compound.

It was because of his municipal programming career that Swanny knew Mawan's underground water systems so well and was able to help reestablish a central government there.

Swanny Mull was described as being short and muscular, with a pale but youthful face. His long, snowy white hair was pulled back with metal clasps.

